.TH "HTMLIMAGEELEMENT.REFERRERPOLICY" "3JS" "November 7, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLImageElement.referrerPolicy \- HTMLImageElement: referrerPolicy
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]referrerPolicy\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLImageElement\f[R] interface defining which referrer is sent
when fetching the resource.
It reflects the \f[CR]<img>\f[R] element\(cqs \f[CR]referrerpolicy\f[R]
content attribute.
.SH VALUE
A string whose value is one of \f[CR]no\-referrer\f[R],
\f[CR]no\-referrer\-when\-downgrade\f[R], \f[CR]origin\f[R],
\f[CR]origin\-when\-cross\-origin\f[R], \f[CR]same\-origin\f[R],
\f[CR]strict\-origin\f[R],
\f[CR]strict\-origin\-when\-cross\-origin\f[R], or
\f[CR]unsafe\-url\f[R].
For their meanings, see the HTML \f[CR]<img>\f[R] reference.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] img = \f[B]new\f[R] Image();
img.src = \(dqimg/logo.png\(dq;
img.referrerPolicy = \(dqorigin\(dq;

\f[B]const\f[R] div = document.getElementById(\(dqdivAround\(dq);
div.appendChild(img); \f[I]// Fetch the image using the origin as the referrer\f[R]
.EE
